        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 8 at 9:03AM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 857 AM EDT, radar indicated scattered lake effect snow showers
moving southeast at 25 mph. Snow showers combined with temperatures
in the 20s are resulting in slick conditions on untreated roadways.

HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Winds gusting to 30 mph...
Visibility dropping to less than one mile at times...

Use caution if traveling this morning. Rapid changes in visibility
and potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.
</description>
